SIMPLE: enthrone
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enthrone
<hw>En*throne"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>en-</ets> + <ets>throne</ets>: cf. OF. <ets>enthroner</ets>. Cf.
<er>Inthronize</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To seat on a throne; to
exalt to the seat of royalty or of high authority; hence, to invest with
sovereign authority or dignity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Beneath a sculptured arch he sits <qex>enthroned</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It [mercy] is <qex>enthroned</qex> in the hearts of kings.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>To induct, as a bishop, into the
powers and privileges of a vacant see.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enthronement</ent>⟦br⟧
